      "title": "The U.S. Department of Justice submitted a Statement of Interest...",
      "content_html": "\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://scontent.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t31.18172-1/cp0/p50x50/21950661_1662566980443451_7358479861831904430_o.jpg?_nc_cat=103\u0026ccb=1-5\u0026_nc_sid=dbb9e7\u0026_nc_ohc=UiIsKtF5zOMAX94BsXs\u0026_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-1.fna\u0026oh=227acdd6bde33da7438f6cb8c432db98\u0026oe=614CD7A1\" alt=\"\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/\"\u003eACLU of Colorado\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/posts/4549676378399149\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ci\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe U.S. Department of Justice submitted a Statement of Interest in our lawsuit against Douglas County Schools and Sheriff's Office for the arrest of A.V., an 11-year-old student with autism. The DOJ undermined Douglas County's motion to dismiss our case, affirming that under the Americans With Disabilities Act, law enforcement have an obligation to make reasonable accommodations when making arrests. They failed to do so. They failed A.V.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.westword.com/news/douglas-county-autistic-child-handcuffed-arrested-video-update-12024464\"\u003eThe child allegedly poked a classmate with a pencil.\u003cimg src=\"https://external.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/safe_image.php?d=AQF0S6EXoroRWX5l\u0026w=540\u0026h=282\u0026url=https%3A%2F%2Fimages1.westword.com%2Fimager%2Fu%2Fslideshow%2F12024470%2Faclu.child.handcuff.video.jpg\u0026cfs=1\u0026upscale=1\u0026fallback=news_d_placeholder_publisher\u0026_nc_oe=6e8e8\u0026_nc_sid=06c271\u0026ccb=3-5\u0026_nc_hash=AQHvGoIN6EvzNorm\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"262\" caption=\"\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003ewestword.com\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eAutistic Child Handcuffing Lawsuit: Feds Disagree With Douglas County\u003c/p\u003eThe child allegedly poked a classmate with a pencil.\u003ca href=\"https://www.westword.com/news/douglas-county-autistic-child-handcuffed-arrested-video-update-12024464\"\u003eThe child allegedly poked a classmate with a pencil.\u003c/a\u003e",
