    {
      "id": "https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/posts/4462914557075332",
      "url": "https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/posts/4462914557075332",
      "title": "Combatting discrimination is essential to our democratic ideals....",
      "content_html": "\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://scontent.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t31.18172-1/cp0/p50x50/21950661_1662566980443451_7358479861831904430_o.jpg?_nc_cat=103\u0026ccb=1-5\u0026_nc_sid=dbb9e7\u0026_nc_ohc=UiIsKtF5zOMAX94BsXs\u0026_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-1.fna\u0026oh=227acdd6bde33da7438f6cb8c432db98\u0026oe=614CD7A1\" alt=\"\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/\"\u003eACLU of Colorado\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/posts/4462914557075332\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ci\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003cp\u003eCombatting discrimination is essential to our democratic ideals. The Tenth Circuit Court of Appeals has recognized in Creative, et al v. Elenis, et al, that there is no constitutional license for the company to discriminate against LGBTQ+ people based on religious beliefs. Refusing a same-sex couple’s request for a website celebrating their wedding but accepting an opposite-sex couple’s identical request is discrimination, plain and simple. The court’s ruling is not just a victory for LGBTQ people, but for anyone who has feared being refused services because of who they are.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.coloradopolitics.com/courts/appeals-court-upholds-colorados-anti-discrimination-act-in-face-of-lgbtq-focused-challenge/article_fcb2fea0-ee89-11eb-a4bb-770cf991622d.html\"\u003eBy a 2-1 decision, a panel of the U.S. Court of Appeals for the 10th Circuit rejected a First Amendment challenge to the Colorado Anti-Discrimination Act from Lorie Smith and\u003cimg src=\"https://external.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/safe_image.php?d=AQExUEwCtqajnQDO\u0026w=540\u0026h=282\u0026url=https%3A%2F%2Fbloximages.newyork1.vip.townnews.com%2Fcoloradopolitics.com%2Fcontent%2Ftncms%2Fassets%2Fv3%2Feditorial%2F6%2F18%2F618920e6-afdc-11e9-97af-9b12266dad0f%2F5d3b55e4e8a6f.image.jpg%3Fresize%3D945%252C630\u0026cfs=1\u0026upscale=1\u0026fallback=news_d_placeholder_publisher\u0026_nc_oe=6e8e7\u0026_nc_sid=06c271\u0026ccb=3-5\u0026_nc_hash=AQETgjzR5AB9UL1p\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"262\" caption=\"\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003ecoloradopolitics.com\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eAppeals court upholds Colorado's anti-discrimination act in face of LGBTQ-focused challenge\u003c/p\u003eBy a 2-1 decision, a panel of the U.S. Court of Appeals for the 10th Circuit rejected a First Amendment challenge to the Colorado Anti-Discrimination Act from Lorie Smith and\u003ca href=\"https://www.coloradopolitics.com/courts/appeals-court-upholds-colorados-anti-discrimination-act-in-face-of-lgbtq-focused-challenge/article_fcb2fea0-ee89-11eb-a4bb-770cf991622d.html\"\u003eBy a 2-1 decision, a panel of the U.S. Court of Appeals for the 10th Circuit rejected a First Amendment challenge to the Colorado Anti-Discrimination Act from Lorie Smith and\u003c/a\u003e",
